author: jason.carver
content:
At least the ping is received, yes. Then `trin` sends a `whoareyou` and `ddht` drops it with:
```
ddht.Session  Session[b897..812d<-|-UNKNOWN@127.0.0.1:4242]: Discarding non MessagePacket: InboundEnvelope(packet=Packet[WhoAreYouPacket](iv=b'E\x0c\xd4\x90\xe7\xca\xc6\xa2\xfa8\xcaf\x1d\xd8\xe6V', header=Header(protocol_id=b'discv5', version=b'\x00\x01', flag=1, aes_gcm_nonce=b'\x00\x00\x00\x0b\x84\xd4$>o\x92\xb3\x96', auth_data_size=24), auth_data=WhoAreYouPacket(id_nonce=b'\x07\xe6`\xf1\x18~\x93{\xdb3c\xb5R\xdbv>', enr_sequence_number=0), message_cipher_text=b'', dest_node_id=b'\xb8\x97\n\xe0\xdf\xc3\xadx\xd4d\xa8\x98\x97\xe2%\xd9ZcG-\x951\x95?\xfc\x1eO\x9dD\x9e\x81-'), sender=127.0.0.1:4242)
ddht.Dispatcher  discarding unhandled inbound envelope InboundEnvelope(packet=Packet[WhoAreYouPacket](iv=b'E\x0c\xd4\x90\xe7\xca\xc6\xa2\xfa8\xcaf\x1d\xd8\xe6V', header=Header(protocol_id=b'discv5', version=b'\x00\x01', flag=1, aes_gcm_nonce=b'\x00\x00\x00\x0b\x84\xd4$>o\x92\xb3\x96', auth_data_size=24), auth_data=WhoAreYouPacket(id_nonce=b'\x07\xe6`\xf1\x18~\x93{\xdb3c\xb5R\xdbv>', enr_sequence_number=0), message_cipher_text=b'', dest_node_id=b'\xb8\x97\n\xe0\xdf\xc3\xadx\xd4d\xa8\x98\x97\xe2%\xd9ZcG-\x951\x95?\xfc\x1eO\x9dD\x9e\x81-'), sender=127.0.0.1:4242)
```
which leaves `trin` repeating:
```
[2021-05-12T17:04:30Z DEBUG discv5::service] NodeId unknown, requesting ENR. Node: 0xb897..812d, addr: 127.0.0.1:44477 
[2021-05-12T17:04:30Z DEBUG discv5::handler] Sending WHOAREYOU to Node: 0xb897..812d, addr: 127.0.0.1:44477
```
